<subSubSection id="C3081DCA611DFFE8FF23FAEF7640C154" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAD4E41611DFFE8FF23FAEF7768C2F4" blockId="15.[192,1440,1315,1596]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FF23FAEF7504C254" bold="true" box="[192,308,1315,1339]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Remark.</emphasis>
Since the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611DFFE8FD9BFAEF77EAC254" authority="Philippi" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1864" box="[632,986,1315,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Schizochelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursulus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FD9BFAEF7744C254" box="[632,884,1315,1339]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Schizochelus ursulus</emphasis>
Philippi
</taxonomicName>
has been lost and the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8333B0611DFFE8FF1EFA8F75AEC234" author="Philippi, R. A." box="[253,414,1347,1371]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="434 - 462" refId="ref19062" refString="Philippi, R. A. 1864. Sobre algunos coleopteros nuevos de Chile de la familia de las melolontideas. Anales de la Universidad Republica de Chile 24: 434 - 462." type="journal article" year="1864">Philippi 1864</bibRefCitation>
) falls within the intraspecific variation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611DFFE8FC6CFA8F70AEC234" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[911,1182,1347,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pristerophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FC6CFA8F70AEC234" box="[911,1182,1347,1371]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pristerophora longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, I am designating the 
<typeStatus id="54A9F0E3611DFFE8FF23FAAF7500C214" box="[192,304,1379,1403]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the latter as the 
<typeStatus id="54A9F0E3611DFFE8FDFFFAA8764DC213" box="[540,637,1380,1404]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">neotype</typeStatus>
of the former. This makes the two names objective synonyms and will eliminate any further use of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611DFFE8FDADFA4F7761C2F4" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1864" box="[590,849,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Schizochelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursulus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FDADFA4F7761C2F4" box="[590,849,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Schizochelus ursulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD4E41611DFFE8FF13FA6F7640C154" blockId="15.[192,1440,1315,1596]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8333B0611DFFE8FF13FA6F7581C2D4" author="Martinez, A." box="[240,433,1443,1467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="47 - 52" refId="ref18806" refString="Martinez, A. 1957. Nuevos generos y especies de Macrodactylini (Col. Scarab. Melolonthinae). Neotropica 3 (11): 47 - 52." type="journal article" year="1957">Martínez (1957)</bibRefCitation>
created the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611DFFE8FD6CFA687778C2D4" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="1957" box="[655,840,1444,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Astaenosiagum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FD6CFA687778C2D4" box="[655,840,1444,1467]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Astaenosiagum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this species when he correctly determined that it belonged in another genus than Brazilian 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611DFFE8FD2DFA0F775AC2B4" authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1850" box="[718,874,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Schizochelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FD2DFA0F775AC2B4" box="[718,874,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Schizochelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8333B0611DFFE8FC94FA0F7008C2B4" author="Martinez, A." box="[887,1080,1475,1499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="47 - 52" refId="ref18806" refString="Martinez, A. 1957. Nuevos generos y especies de Macrodactylini (Col. Scarab. Melolonthinae). Neotropica 3 (11): 47 - 52." type="journal article" year="1957">Martínez (1957)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention the other two species here placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611DFFE8FE26FA2F765AC294" box="[453,618,1507,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pristerophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FE26FA2F765AC294" box="[453,618,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pristerophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species share many characteristics with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611DFFE8FB70FA2F7190C294" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[1171,1440,1507,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pristerophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="B9669253611DFFE8FB70FA2F7190C294" box="[1171,1440,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pristerophora longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that warrant their inclusion in the same genus. Notably, the structure of the male genitalia in all three species is very similar (Figs. 15-17).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
